    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-05-14T18:50:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-05-14T18:50:00-05:00" n="891"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d891">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">795.00/5–1454: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Korea</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d891fn1">This telegram was drafted by <persName
                            corresp="#p_MRJG1">McClurkin</persName> and cleared by
                            <persName>Drumright</persName>.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret<lb/>limit distribution</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-05-14T19:50:00-04:00"
                            >May 14, 1954—7:50 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>924. Your 1141.<note n="2" xml:id="d891fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">
                            <ref target="#d891">Supra</ref>
                        </hi>.</note> We have received following information from Defense which
                    provides partial answer questions raised reference telegram. No doubt <persName
                        corresp="#p_TLGMD1">General Taylor</persName> can provide detailed
                    information his actions implement this policy. You may consider it desirable
                    arrange with <persName corresp="#p_TLGMD1">General Taylor</persName> for you and
                    him to talk with President <persName corresp="#p_RS1">Rhee</persName> or
                        <persName corresp="#p_SWIA1">Sohn</persName> or both about this policy.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_CINCFE1">CINCFE</gloss> is under instructions support and
                        maintain 20 Division <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> Army.</item>
                    <pb facs="0675" n="1793" xml:id="pg_1793"/>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_CINCFE1">CINCFE</gloss> has submitted proposed tables
                        organization and equipment for 20 Division force. These proposed tables were
                        drawn up in conformity with certain <gloss target="#t_JCS1">JCS</gloss>
                        criteria for equipping foreign forces and in light of foreseeable matériel
                        and funds available <gloss target="#t_CINCFE1">CINCFE</gloss>.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>After proposed tables reviewed here <gloss target="#t_CINCFE1"
                            >CINCFE</gloss> was advised of further reductions to be made to
                        eliminate specific non-essential units and equipment unless he could provide
                        justification to contrary. Subject these specified modifications <gloss
                            target="#t_CINCFE1">CINCFE</gloss> was authorized put proposed tables
                        into effect.</item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>In general terms decision organize and equip <gloss target="#t_ROK1"
                            >ROK</gloss> forces on more austere basis than U.S. units was made in
                        recognition of following two facts: <list>
                            <label>a.</label>
                            <item>Certain service and support units normally part U.S. formations
                                are not essential to effectiveness <gloss target="#t_ROK1"
                                    >ROK</gloss> forces which can be streamlined compared U.S.
                                standards.</item>
                            <label>b.</label>
                            <item>Equipment and logistic support 20 <gloss target="#t_ROK1"
                                    >ROK</gloss> Divisions on U.S. standards would jeopardize other
                                essential U.S. military commitments.</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>Four specific factors necessitate organization and maintenance <gloss
                            target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> forces on relative austere basis: <list>
                            <label>a.</label>
                            <item>Probable future availability funds and equipment.</item>
                            <label>b.</label>
                            <item>Budgetary limitations.</item>
                            <label>c.</label>
                            <item>Other world-wide commitments.</item>
                            <label>d.</label>
                            <item>Status U.S. reserves of equipment.</item>
                        </list>
                    </item>
                    <label>6.</label>
                    <item>
                        <gloss target="#t_CINCFE1">CINCFE</gloss> and 8th Army are of course
                        continuing follow their present instructions to support 20 Division <gloss
                            target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> Army. Problem they face is how force should
                        be composed. 8th Army has been experimenting for months devise prototype
                            <gloss target="#t_ROK1">ROK</gloss> division that can have maximum
                        military effect with minimum logistic investment. Any “cutting to the bone”
                        such as mentioned in reference telegram applies this effort and does not
                        pertain to reduction over-all 20 division level.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
